        <h1>Coronavirus</h1>
        </div>
        </div>
        <section class="sidebar-interior"><div class="row">
        <div class="intetior-sidebar-cntnt">
        <div class="large-12 columns"> 


    

    
        <div class="row">
            <div class="medium-8 columns">
                <p><img src="/AVcoronavirus.jpg?Action=thumbnail&amp;algorithm=fill_proportional&amp;width=600" width="600"></p>
                <p><strong>Last Updated: Tuesday, April 14, 2020</strong>
                    <br></p>
                <hr>
<p style="background-color: rgb(251, 213, 181);"><strong>From the District:</strong> </p>
                <p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><em><a href="/LiteratureRetrieve.aspx?ID=210866">Continuity of Education Plan</a></em></strong><strong><em><a href="/LiteratureRetrieve.aspx?ID=210859"><br><br>Extended Meal Service Information</a></em></strong><strong><em> </em></strong>                    <strong><em><br>__________________________________</em></strong> <strong><em> </em></strong><strong><em> </em></strong> </p>
<strong> </strong><strong><em>UPDATE - <span style="background-color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"><span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span>April 14, 2020<span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span></span></em></strong>
                <br><p>Today, Allegheny Valley families received a Blackboard Connect message that provided information on grading for the fourth quarter. 
                    The links for the high school and elementary schools are below.  If you should have any questions or concerns, please contact
                    your child's administrator or counselor.  </p>
<a href="https://youtu.be/iKn75Hnwafw">Springdale Jr-Sr High School grading</a>                                    
                <br><br><a href="https://youtu.be/6oQoJF74EG4">Acmetonia Elementary School gradin<strong><em>g</em></strong></a>
                <br><p><strong>Principal Contact Information: </strong>
                    <br><em>Springdale Jr-Sr High School -</em>
                    <br>  Andrew Leviski     <a href="mailto:aleviski@avsd.k12.pa.us">aleviski@avsd.k12.pa.us</a>
                    <br>  Peter Simpson        <a href="mailto:psimpson@avsd.k12.pa.us">psimpson@avsd.k12.pa.us</a>
                    <br><br><em>Acmetonia Elementary School: </em>
                    <br>  Gregory Heavner   <a href="mailto:gheavner@avsd.k12.pa.us">gheavner@avsd.k12.pa.us</a>
                    <br>  Jennifer Vecchio    <a href="mailto:jvecchio@avsd.k12.pa.us">jvecchio@avsd.k12.pa.us</a>
                    <br></p>
                <p><strong style="background-color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"><em><span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span>April 9, 2020<span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span></em></strong>
                    <br><br>This morning, Governor Wolf announced the closure of all Pennsylvania school districts for the remainder of the 2019-2020 year. The
                    decision was made in consultation with the Departments of Education and Health, based on the most recent information regarding COVID-19
                    and the safety and welfare of students, staff, and the community.
                    <br><br>The Allegheny Valley School District will provide additional information next week about online learning, events, and other changes
                    that students and parents can expect for the remaining weeks of the school year.
                    <br><br>We hope the community understands how difficult this decision is for all of us; we would love to have our students back in school.
                    However, following the decision of the Governor is the best alternative for the health of students, staff, and community </p>
                <p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><em> <span style="background-color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"><span style="color: rgb(191, 191, 191);">x</span>April 7, 2020<span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span></span><br></em></strong>                    </p>The Pennsylvania Department of Education has all school districts submit a Continuity of Education Plan to explain how it will
                provide education for students during this shut down.   Allegheny Valley has submitted <a href="/LiteratureRetrieve.aspx?ID=210866">the attached plan</a>. 
                <br><br><p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><em><span style="background-color: rgb(216, 216, 216); color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"><span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"></span></span><span style="background-color: rgb(216, 216, 216);"><span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span>March 30, 2020<span style="color: rgb(216, 216, 216);">x</span></span></em></strong>
                    <br><br>Dear Parents/Guardians:
                    <br><br>As you may have heard, another mandate was given today from the Governor to extend school closures, this time indefinitely. Although
                    it is disappointing to lose more of the school year, the outcome this measure supports will be worth it for all of us.
                    <br><br>Let’s look at the positives: our community has definitely lived up to its Dynamo nickname. People are helping each other, sharing kindness
                    to weather the difficulties. Our medical personnel, first responders, and necessary work force continue to operate to help us through
                    this emergency. In the District, an Extended Meal Program services students, communication continues, and online remote learning has
                    begun.
                    <br><br>While all events throughout the rest of the school year are under discussion by the administration, we remain optimistic. With the
                    timeline for the closure unknown, it is difficult to make any concrete plans. However, the intent remains to hold major District events
                    when possible. All decisions on events will be made when the situation becomes more stable.
                    <br><br>We know that there are many more questions than answers. At a time when so much is unknown, we have faith that what is important will
                    endure.
                    <br><br>A number of years ago, the District had for its annual theme “Together, we can.” The motto stressed the fact that together the Allegheny
                    Valley Community could get through anything. That thought holds true today, especially in a time different from any we have known.
                    We can get through this, we will get through this, together.
                    <br><br>In the meantime, we can’t stress enough to continue social distancing and other preventative measures. Take care of your families,
                    your neighbors, and yourselves.
                    <br><br>Sincerely,
                    <br>Patrick M. Graczyk, Ed.D.
                    <br>Superintendent
                    <br></p>
                <br><p><strong style="background-color: rgb(250, 192, 143);"><a href="http://www.avsdweb.org/coronaviruslog%20"><span style="color: rgb(250, 192, 143);">xx</span>Information LOG<span style="color: rgb(250, 192, 143);">xx</span></a></strong>
                    <br></p>
                <br><hr>
<p style="background-color: rgb(251, 213, 181);"><strong>Communication From the District:   </strong> </p>
